CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 22, 1955, pg. 9, reads: "'We're After Five Million Too!' - Mrs. George L. West, fourth from the left, president of the Pittsburgh YWCA, tells Mrs. Laurance S. Rockefeller that the Pittsburgh Association has on a five million dollar drive also. Mrs. Rockefeller, chairman of the Centennial Observance of the YWCA of the United States, is heading a drive for a similar amount for the National YWCA.  Seated, left to right: Mrs. W. Sherman Skinner, Mrs. William M. Cuthbert, Mrs. Edward W. Macy, Mrs. West and Mrs. Rockefeller. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Four women holding candles to three tiered cake inscribed "100 YWCA 1855-1955 Centennial," at YWCA banquet
